               <msContents>
                  <summary>I) Maṣḥafa gәbra ḥǝmāmāt “Book of the Rite of the Holy Week (fols.
                     4ra-153rc)”:&#xD; I-1) Introduction (fols. 4ra-6ra)&#xD; I-2) Eve of Palm
                     Sunday (fols. 6ra-8rb)&#xD; I-3) Palm Sunday (fols. 8rb-14rc)&#xD; I-4) Monday
                     (fols. 14rc-30rb)&#xD; - Night hours (fols. 14rc-16rc)&#xD; - Day hours (fols.
                     16rc-30rb), including: Homily by John Chrysostom for Monday morning (fols.
                     19vc-20vc); Homily by John Chrysostom on the fig tree for Monday morning (fols.
                     20vc-24rb)&#xD; I-5) Tuesday (fols. 30rb-45rc)&#xD; - Night hours (fols.
                     30rb-32va)&#xD; - Day hours (fols. 32va-45rc)&#xD; I-6) Wednesday (fols.
                     45rc-57va)&#xD; - Night hours (fols. 45rc-47rc)&#xD; - Day hours (fols.
                     47rc-57va)&#xD; I-7) Thursday (fols. 57va-76ara)&#xD; - Night hours (fols.
                     57va-59vb)&#xD; - Day hours (fols. 59vb-76ara)&#xD; I-8) Friday (fols.
                     76ara-124ra)&#xD; - Night hours (fols. 76ara-85ra)&#xD; - Day hours (fols.
                     85ra-124ra), including: Homily by Jacob of Serug on Abraham (fols.
                     98vc-103vc)&#xD; I-9) Saturday (fols. 124ra-145va)&#xD; - Night hours (fols.
                     124ra-136rc), including: Rāʾǝya Yoḥannǝs “Revelation of John” (fols.
                     126rc-136ra)&#xD; - Mass (fols. 136rc-144ra), including: Tǝmhǝrta ḫǝbuʾāt
                     “Teaching of Mysteries” (fols. 142vb-144ra)&#xD; - Evening (fols.
                     144ra-145va)&#xD; I-10) Homily of Cyriacus the Bishop of Behnesa [Lāḥā Māryām
                     “Lamentation of Mary”] (fols. 145vb-153rc)&#xD; &#xD; Additiones 1-3.</summary>
