                        <seg type="rubrication">Holy names; name of the donors.&#xD; Six lines in
                           the incipit page of Text I-1 (fol. 4r), in three groups, alternating with
                           black lines; incipits of the texts, their sections and subsections; six
                           lines in the incipit page of the section “Friday morning” (Text I-8), in
                           three groups, alternating with black lines.&#xD; Titles of the Biblical
                           books and other works; names of Hebrew letters in Text I-8; abbreviations
                           in Text I-7 and Text I-8; the beginning word of each paragraph in the
                           text “Tǝmhǝrta ḫǝbuʾāt” within Text I-9; the words yǝbe in Text I-4 (esp.
                           fols. 17vb-18rc) and Text I-6 (esp. fols. 53vc-54ra); the words
                           yǝtaragwǝm in Text I-6 and Text I-8, matargwam in Text I-8,
                           wa-yǝbal/wa-yǝbalu in Text I-8, ṣallǝyu in Text I-9.&#xD; Elements of the
                           punctuation signs; Ethiopic numerals or their elements; elements of the
                           text dividers.</seg>

                     
