                     mentioned: his mother Walatta Śǝllāse, his wife Walatta Māryām, his children
                     Gabra Ḥǝywat, Walda Gabrǝʾel, ʾArʾāyā Śǝllāse.&#xD; Names of other individuals
                     are written in some supplication formulas: Gabra Śǝllāse (esp. <locus target="#6ra">6ra</locus> l.10, 136ra l.17, 150rc l.32) and Walda Māryām
                     (<locus target="#24rb">24rb</locus> ls.9-10, 91rb l.31, 144vb ls.6-7). In
                     two supplication formulas “people of the place” (sabʾā hagar) (esp. <locus target="#29vb">29vb</locus>) and as the “people of the place, children of
                     the community” (sabʾā hagar dāqiqā māḫbar) are mentioned (esp. <locus target="#153rc">153rc</locus>).</provenance>
